<p><strong>NOTICE TO SIGNERS:</strong> This is a non-binding, advisory petition intended to express the will of Maryland voters to the Maryland General Assembly and other public officials. This petition is not a statutory referendum, does not invoke Article XVI of the Maryland Constitution, and does not itself enact or repeal any law.</p><p> </p><p><strong>PREAMBLE</strong><br />WHEREAS, Article 13 of the Declaration of Rights of the Maryland Constitution states, “That every man (<em>and</em><br /><em>woman</em>) hath a right to petition the Legislature for the redress of grievances in a peaceable and orderly manner”<br />(italics added, as affirmed by Article 46 of the Declaration of Rights); and<br />WHEREAS, the First Amendment to the United States Constitution guarantees the right of the people to<br />petition the government for a redress of grievances; and<br />WHEREAS, free, fair, and transparent elections are the cornerstone of representative democracy; and<br />WHEREAS, Maryland voters must have confidence that elections are conducted lawfully, securely, and<br />uniformly, and that only eligible voters are registered and permitted to cast ballots; and<br />WHEREAS, the General Assembly of Maryland has considered legislation known as the Secure the Vote Act of<br />2026;NOW, THEREFORE, we, the undersigned residents and voters of the State of Maryland, respectfully petition<br />the Maryland General Assembly to enact the Secure the Vote Act of 2026, including the following provisions:</p><p> </p><p><strong>PETITIONED PROVISIONS</strong><br />1. Repeal ballot drop box mandates, including at correctional facilities, and prohibit absentee ballot<br />return via drop boxes.<br />2. Restrict absentee voting to voters unable to vote in person for enumerated reasons and repeal<br />permanent absentee status.<br />3. Require voter identification for inperson voting, with government-issued Real I.D..<br />4. Require proof of U.S. citizenship for voter registration.<br />5. Mandate regular audits of the statewide voter registration list and public reporting of results.<br />6. Require signature verification and signed eligibility oaths for absentee ballots.<br />7. Apply uniform election standards to municipal elections, including voter registration, ID, audits, and<br />ballot security.<br />8. Prohibit nonU.S. citizens from registering or voting in municipal elections.</p><p> </p><p><strong>CONCLUSION</strong><br />By signing below, we affirm this petition is submitted peaceably and lawfully in accordance with our<br />constitutional rights, and we urge the Maryland General Assembly to enact the Secure the Vote Act of 2026.</p>								</div>
